28/10/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The Central Electoral Commission (CEC) says the United States has offered to supply monitors for the 7 November referendum on the new decentralisation laws. CEC spokesman Zoran Tanevski said on Wednesday (27 October) that the US Embassy is willing to deploy 49 observers in parallel to the monitoring missions of the ODIHR and the NGO MOST. He noted that it was the first time the US Embassy has sought a direct deployment of observers. (Dnevnik - 28/10/04; A1 TV - 27/10/04)
